<paragraph blockId="37.[826,1441,1619,1702]" pageId="37" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis box="[826,952,1619,1640]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="536">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin root-word 
<emphasis box="[1012,1058,1650,1671]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="536">flexi</emphasis>
meaning to bend, referring to the unique shape of the aedeagal shaft.
